Therefore, it is only a question of degree how far the government should permit the amalgamation and should declare these roads to be for the general advantage of Canada. If they are all amalgamated, they are for the general advantage of Canada, and if only a part of them are amalgamated, they are for the general advantage of Canada. These questions have all, I am sure, been considered by the Railway Committee, and I have always made it a rule to support the report of the Railway Committee unless there are strong reasons to the contrary.
